        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-27T05:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-27T05:30:00-05:00" n="23"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conference 180.03101/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary’s Notes of a Conversation held in M. <persName
                            corresp="#p_PS1">Pichon</persName>’s Room at the Quai d’Orsay, Paris, on
                        Monday, January 27th, 1919, at 10:30 a.m.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="right">B. C. 11</p>
                <list type="participants">
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Present</hi>.—<hi rend="italic">America, United States
                            of:</hi> President <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>, Mr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_LR1">R. Lansing</persName>, Mr. <persName>A. H.
                            Frazier</persName>, Mr. <persName>L. Harrison</persName>, <persName>Col.
                            R. H. Williams</persName>.—<hi rend="italic">British Empire:</hi> The
                        Rt. Hon. <persName corresp="#p_LGD1">D. Lloyd George</persName>, M.P., The
                        Rt. Hon. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">A. J. Balfour</persName>, M.P., Lt.
                        Col. Sir <persName corresp="#p_HLCSM1">M. P. A. Hankey</persName>, K.C.B.,
                        Captain <persName>E. Abraham</persName>, Mr. <persName>H. [E.]
                            Phipps</persName>.—<hi rend="italic">France:</hi> M. <persName
                            corresp="#p_CGEB1">Clemenceau</persName>, M. <persName corresp="#p_PS1"
                            >Pichon</persName>, <persName>M. Dutasta</persName>, <persName>M.
                            Berthelot</persName>, Capt. <persName>Portier</persName>.—<hi
                            rend="italic">Italy:</hi> M. <persName corresp="#p_OVE1"
                            >Orlando</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SSB1">Baron
                            Sonnino</persName>, Major <persName>Jones</persName>.—<hi rend="italic"
                            >Japan:</hi>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MNB1">Baron Makino</persName>, <persName>H. E. M.
                            Matsui</persName>, <persName>M. Saburi</persName>.—<hi rend="italic"
                            >Interpreter</hi>—Professor <persName>P. J. Mantoux</persName>.</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p rend="center">Representation at Prince’s Island of the small States in formation,
                    whose territories previously belonged to the Russian Empire</p>
                <p>9. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Balfour</hi>
                    </persName> said that he wished to raise a point which he thought had been
                    settled, but of which he could find no record in the Minutes. He wished to know
                    whether those elements of Old Russia which, we hoped, would succeed in forming
                    se[parate states?] such as Esthonia, Georgia, possibly Russian Armenia and
                    Daghestan, were invited to the meeting on Prince’s Island.</p>
                <p>(It was decided … that all such elements, unless expressly excluded, were invited
                    to attend.)</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1919-01-27T10:30:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">27 January, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
